'''Tsukimoto Shrine''' (槻本神社) is a [[Shinto shrine]] located in [[Takayama City]], [[Gifu Prefecture]]. It is identified as the {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|qq=draft|1=Shikinaisha|qq=draft|qq=draft}} "Tsukimoto Shrine" in the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|ja|延喜式神名帳|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|qq=draft|qq=draft}} for [[Hida Province]]'s {{ill|Ōno District (Gifu)|ja|大野郡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
The shrine's sacred cedar tree ({{ill|Cryptomeria|ja|スギ|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) is designated as a Gifu Prefecture Natural Monument.<ref name="sugi">{{Cite web|language=ja|date= |url=http://www.pref.gifu.lg.jp/kyoiku-bunka-sports/bunka-geijutsu/bunkazai-zuroku/bunkazai-zuroku/tenki/takayamsi/tukimoto.html |title=Tsukimoto Shrine's Cedar Tree |publisher=Gifu Prefecture |accessdate=2013-04-20}}</ref> The tree is estimated to be over 1,200 years old, and local lore warns that those who harm it will quickly fall ill and die.
== History == The date of the shrine's founding is unknown. According to legend, the original sacred object was a giant {{ill|Zelkova|ja|ケヤキ|qq=draft|qq=draft}} tree (槻), which continued to exist even after the construction of the shrine buildings. Another version of the legend attributes the sacred status to a giant cedar tree instead of a zelkova.
The current shrine structure was rebuilt in the 5th year of {{ill|Genbun era|ja|元文|1=Genbun|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (1740). In the 4th year of the [[Meiji era]] (1871), the shrine was designated as a {{ill|Gōsha|ja|郷社|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
